extend partials/mainLayout

block title
  title Documentation Icon Font - #{iconFont.name} - by Pixeden.

block header
  header#top-bar
    .container
      img(src='assets/img/logo.png',alt='logo')

block hero
  section#hero_box
    .container
      h1.refs-title Documentation
      p You will find in this document details on how to use our icon font and a list of useful helper classes.



block content

  section#docs_box
    .container


      section#default-css
        h2.page-header Add our icon font 
          small to your website
        ol
          li Copy the entire 
            code #{iconFont.cssName}
            |  directory into your project.
          li In the 
            code &lt;head&gt;
            |  of your html, reference the location to our icon font CSS: 
            span.italic #{iconFont.cssName}.css
            | and if needed helper CSS: 
            span.italic helper.css
            | .
            pre
              code &lt;link rel=&quot;stylesheet&quot; href=&quot;path/to/#{iconFont.cssName}/css/#{iconFont.cssName}.css&quot;&gt;
                | &#13;
                | &lt;!-- Optional - Adds useful class to manipulate icon font display --&gt;
                | &lt;link rel=&quot;stylesheet&quot; href=&quot;path/to/#{iconFont.cssName}/css/helper.css&quot;&gt;
      
      


      section#inline
        h2.page-header Place the icons 
          small in your HTML

        .row
          .col-md-3.col-sm-4
            p
              span(class='#{docs.inline[0]}')  #{docs.inline[0]}
              br
              i(class='#{docs.inline[1]}')  #{docs.inline[1]}
          .col-md-9.col-sm-8
            p Easiest way is to place your icon inline using a html tag such as 
              code &lt;span&gt; 
              |  or 
              code &lt;i&gt;
              pre
                code &lt;span class=&quot;#{docs.inline[0]}&quot;&gt;&lt;/span&gt; #{docs.inline[0]}
                  | &lt;i class=&quot;#{docs.inline[1]}&quot;&gt;&lt;/span&gt; #{docs.inline[1]}

            .alert.alert-success
              i(class="#{docs.alert[0]} pe-lg") 
              |  icon unicode is added with CSS and the pseudo-class :before.




      section#icomoon
        h2.page-header Compatible with Icomoon 
          small font creator tool
        p The IcoMoon app lets you build and use your own icon sets: 
          a(target="_blank",href="http://icomoon.io/app/") IcoMoon App
          | .
          br
          | You can import 
          code icomoon/*selection.json*
          | in the IcoMoon app using the *Import Icons* button (or via Main Menu &gt; Manage Projects) to retrieve this specific icon font.
          br
          | This way you can mix and match our icon font with other fonts or select only the icons you need and generate a new font.





      
      section#helper
        h2.page-header
          | Helper classes 
          small
            | based on font-awesome useful classes 
            span.italic (optional)
        p
          | Below you will find a list of useful classes to modify the icon display, layout, sizes etc... They come with the helper.css file and are based on a modified version of font-awesome classes.
          strong Important: 
          span.italic
            |  if you already use font-awesome (FA) icon font in your website, you might want to delete the classes in the helper file under 
            code /* FA based classes */
            |  and use the FA classes instead.


  


      section#larger
